Coloured in mingled shades of white and pale blue, its snowy appearance blends perfectly in the coldest biomes. Panels of coarse, thin leather line its exterior, save for the joints which are covered by lightly-padded wool to allow a full range of movement. Layers of cloth beneath this exterior keep the wearer warm and comfortable for extended periods of time, and its enchantments are strong enough to keep the worst chills at bay. The boots, equipped with metal spurs and netted snowshoes, can easily negotiate alpine terrain while the network of belts and bandoliers across the torso and limbs give the wearer easy access to whatever tools may be required on long journeys.

The designer could not help but remember a certain white-clad Shevarashan, and it is from his memory of her that he so named the outfit.

This white rothe wool mask, accompanied by a shell-like cap crafted from the skull of a black dragon and a pair of manticore leather goggles, completely covers the wearer's face. Padded on the inside for comfort and warmth, it is enchanted to impart a strong protection against the cold over the wearer's vitals. However, the insulative properties and flammable lining make attacks by fire particularly perilous for the wearer.

The designer could not help but remember a certain white-clad Shevarashan, and it is from his memory of her that he so named this piece.

A new Opal adorns the centrepiece of this amulet of faith. A perfect circle with hints of nearly every color forming a mixed rainbow effect. The chain of Platinum clearly shows its age in comparison, orginally a gift from his Father after his second birthday.

Slightly longer then your standard short sword, this double edged sword comes in at 21 inches giving it the appearance of a longsword in its Koboldian makers hands. The crossguard appears to be more ceremonial then practical with 6 gilded spokes. The handle is wrapped in black dye Rothe leather. The pommel forms a simple perfect circle, only adorned by the engraving of the letter R, a mark of its maker.

A gift from Val, this thick cloak is embroidened with runes to imbue the wearer with an unnatural level of protection. A faint flicker of light occassionally glints from the cloak as the light catches a particle of diamond dust leftover from the enchanting process.

This heavy adamantine harness was forged by the steady hand of an experienced armourer. All craftdwarfship is of the highest quality. It is decorated with ornate, golden imagery that makes it nearly resemble chapel mural, with various Dwarven figures following along runic patterns.

This helmet seems to have been fashioned to have a bird-like mask over it, with large crystals to see out of. Enchanted and dyed, the inside of the helmet has a symbol of Tymora engraved upon it, along with two blunt hooks on either side of the chin where a cloth could be strapped.
